-- London Police Say 32 Arrested in Connection With Fee Protest by Students
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2010-11-10T20:00:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/london-police-say-32-arrested-in-connection-with-fee-protest-by-students.html
London’s Metropolitan Police said 32
people have been arrested today in connection with a protest by
students at the complex housing the headquarters of U.K. Prime
Minister  David Cameron ’s Conservative Party.  Seven police officers and seven protesters were injured
none seriously, a spokesman for the police said by telephone.  The students were protesting against plans to cut funding
to universities and raise tuition fees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ben Martin  in London at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net . 